title: Monday Blues: You will not believe the real reason why award winning RnB star Freddie Jackson came to Kenya
text:
By Stevens Muendo Monday, Oct 19th 2015 at 10:16 RnB star Freddie Jackson Photo: singersroom.com 
American rhythm and blues crooner, Freddie Jackson, came to Kenya on an invitation by prominent investor and celebrated polo player Raphael Nzomo who was celebrating his 50th birthday. 
Nzomo, who was accompanied by his wife Patricia, joined the veteran singer on stage during the Saturday night show at Carnivore. Tickets were going for Sh20,000. 
The emcee of the night, Maina Kageni, said Nzomo had invited Freddie Jackson for his birthday show before sharing the idea of having him perform for the public. JOIN THE CONVERSATION
